ss loading, especially with AntClassLoader. If it creates a separate copy, the static methods might not update in our test class. I think I should focus on simplifying my assertions to check for exceptions and ensure setProject is called as needed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preventing Ant from running tests**\\n\\nI need to stop Ant from executing all JUnit4 tests in FormatterElementTest. If Ant sees the test name with FormatterElementTest, it could recognize the @org.junit.Test annotation, but our JUnit5 methods won’t be recognized because of the different annotations. I’ll need to add a dummy method, public void antJUnitCanRunThisClass() {}, and remember that JUnit4 also requires a no-arg public constructor. In our JUnit5 test, we create JUnitTask, add a new test, and set the project to ensure it runs the right test method.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nv77TF6IhYpNnagBRaIHQLMg|fc_05805a539ead06cf016a2637dd971c8194948a7b1a5759888a", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "../../source_context/org.apache.ant/ant-junit/1.10.15/main/extracted/org/apache/tools/ant/taskdefs/optional/junit/JUnitResultFormatter.java", "offset": 1, "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 973, "output": 1215, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31884, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780889534970, "responseId": "resp_05805a539ead06cf016a2637bfcc4c8194b98501762099c7cd"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_nv77TF6IhYpNnagBRaIHQLMg|fc_05805a539ead06cf016a2637dd971c8194948a7b1a5759888a", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n *  Licensed to the Apache Software Foundation (ASF) under one or more\n *  contributor license agreements.  See the NOTICE file distributed with\n *  this work for additional information regarding copyright ownership.\n *  The ASF licenses this file to You under the Apache License, Version 2.0\n *  (the \"License\"); you may not use this file except in compliance with\n *  the License.  You may obtain a copy of the License at\n *\n *      https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n *\n *  Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n *  distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n *  WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n *  See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n *  limitations under the License.\n *\n */\n\npackage org.apache.tools.ant.taskdefs.optional.junit;\n\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\n\nimport junit.framework.TestListener;\n\nimport org.apache.tools.ant.BuildException;\n\n/**\n * This Interface describes classes that format the results of a JUnit\n * testrun.\n *\n */\npublic interface JUnitResultFormatter\n    extends TestListener, JUnitTaskMirror.JUnitResultFormatterMirror {\n    /**\n     * The whole testsuite started.\n     * @param suite the suite.\n     * @throws BuildException on error.\n     */\n    void startTestSuite(JUnitTest suite) throws BuildException;\n\n    /**\n     * The whole testsuite ended.\n     * @param suite the suite.\n     * @throws BuildException on error.\n     */\n    void endTestSuite(JUnitTest suite) throws BuildException;\n\n    /**\n     * Sets the stream the formatter is supposed to write its results to.\n     * @param out the output stream to use.\n     */\n    void setOutput(OutputStream out);\n\n    /**\n     * This is what the test has written to System.out\n     * @param out the string to write.\n     */\n    void setSystemOutput(String out);\n\n    /**\n     * This is what the test has written to System.err\n     * @param err the string to write.\n     */\n    void setSystemError(String err);\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780889566014}]}
